# Cursor Plan Todo Rule

When creating or updating `.cursor/plans/*.plan.md`, make YAML frontmatter `todos` the source of truth. Markdown task lists may mirror the YAML, but must not replace it.

## Required Shape

```yaml
---
name: short-kebab-name
overview: One sentence describing goal and scope.
isProject: false
todos:
  - id: stable-kebab-id
    content: One executable delivery or verification item.
    status: pending
---
```

## Rules

- Use only `pending`, `completed`, or `cancelled` for `status`.
- Keep each `id` stable, kebab-case, and unique within the plan.
- Keep each `content` item specific enough to verify.
- Update `status` in YAML first; sync mirrored Markdown checkboxes only when useful.
- Preserve existing todo IDs referenced by `.cursor/plans/INDEX.md`.
- Do not add plan files just to preserve chat output; only write them when explicitly requested.
